-{zh-cn:'''北面'''（英语：{{Lang|en|The North Face}}）;zh-hk:'''The North Face''';zh-tw:'''The North Face''';zh-sg:'''The North Face''';zh-my:'''The North Face'''}-是一家[[美国|美国]]的[[户外运动|户外运动]]产品公司，生产服装、鞋类和户外设备。该公司总部位于[[加利福尼亚州|加利福尼亚州]]的[[阿拉米達_(加利福尼亞州)|阿拉米达]]，与其兄弟公司[[JanSport|JanSport]]的总部位于同一地点<ref name="Horovitz">{{Cite news|url=https://www.usatoday.com/money/industries/retail/2007-08-19-backpack_N.htm|title=New 'badge' of cool: High-tech, high-fashion backpacks|author=Horovitz|first=Bruce|date=2007-08-20|work=USA Today|accessdate=2009-09-01|page=1A|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090819153415/http://www.usatoday.com/money/industries/retail/2007-08-19-backpack_N.htm|archive-date=2009-08-19|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 历史 ==
北面成立于1966年，最初是[[旧金山|旧金山]]的一家[[攀岩|攀岩]]器材零售店，由{{Le|道格拉斯·汤普金斯|Douglas Tompkins}}和他的妻子{{Le|苏西·汤普金斯|Susie Tompkins Buell}}创办<ref name="Finz2012">{{Cite news|author=Finz|first=Stacey|title=Business booming for once-troubled North Face|url=http://www.sfgate.com/business/article/Business-booming-for-once-troubled-North-Face-3466174.php|accessdate=2015-12-10|work=SF Gate|publisher=San Francisco Chronicle|date=2012-04-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151211012102/http://www.sfgate.com/business/article/Business-booming-for-once-troubled-North-Face-3466174.php|archive-date=2015-12-11|dead-url=no}}</ref>。在[[北半球|北半球]]，高峰的北面因缺少阳光而常年被冰雪覆盖从而难以攀爬，公司取名“北面”即为挑战极限<ref>{{Cite web|title=How ‘The North Face’ Got Its Name|url=https://medium.com/the-north-face/how-the-north-face-got-its-name-8281934a4520|accessdate=2021-01-20|date=2016-12-21|last=Face|first=The North|work=Medium|language=en|archive-date=2021-01-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210127222615/https://medium.com/the-north-face/how-the-north-face-got-its-name-8281934a4520}}</ref>。公司于两年后被肯尼斯·克洛普（{{Lang|en|Kenneth "Hap" Klopp}}）收购<ref name="Finz2012" /><ref name="Bruce B. Johnson's History of Gear webpage">{{Cite web|title=Bruce B. Johnson's History of Gear webpage|url=http://www.oregonphotos.com/The-North-Face-1.html|access-date=2012-11-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120615114914/http://www.oregonphotos.com/The-North-Face-1.html|archive-date=2012-06-15|dead-url=no}}</ref>。2000年，北面被[[威富公司|威富公司]]以2540万[[美元|美元]]收购，北面成为后者的全资子公司<ref name="VF acquisition">{{Cite web|title=The North Face Acquired by VF Corp. in $25.4M Cash Deal|url=https://www.sportsbusinessdaily.com/Daily/Issues/2000/04/10/Finance/THE-NORTH-FACE-ACQUIRED-BY-VF-CORP-IN-$254M-CASH-DEAL.aspx|accessdate=2019-05-19|date=2000-04-10|publisher=[[先進出版公司|Sports Business Daily]]|language=En|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190519081106/https://www.sportsbusinessdaily.com/Daily/Issues/2000/04/10/Finance/THE-NORTH-FACE-ACQUIRED-BY-VF-CORP-IN-$254M-CASH-DEAL.aspx|archive-date=2019-05-19|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.vfc.com/news/vf-in-the-news%3Fnws_id%3D83925AE9-7D1F-F0CC-E043-A740E3EAF0CC |title=VF Corporation – VF in the News |access-date=2019-06-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131102030626/http://www.vfc.com/news/vf-in-the-news%3Fnws_id%3D83925AE9-7D1F-F0CC-E043-A740E3EAF0CC |archive-date=2013-11-02 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。

==争议==

2008年12月，北面向[[美国密苏里东区联邦地区法院|美国密苏里东区联邦地区法院]]提起诉讼，起诉{{Le|The South Butt|The South Butt}}、其创始人小詹姆斯·A·温克尔曼（{{Lang|en|James a . Winkelmann Jr.}}）以及一家负责该公司营销策划的公司。在诉讼中，北面控訴{{Lang|en|The South Butt}}侵犯其[[商标权|商标权]]，并寻求禁令救济<ref>{{Cite web|title=The North Face is suing The South Butt International clothing company accuses teen's Ladue-based operation of trademark infringement|url=http://www.stltoday.com/business/the-north-face-is-suing-the-south-butt-international-clothing/article_f01545a8-383c-5bc6-9d73-fb889ae2569c.html|accessdate=2012-10-20|author=Frankel|date=2009-12-15|first=Todd C.|publisher=STLtoday.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190531172121/https://www.stltoday.com/business/the-north-face-is-suing-the-south-butt-international-clothing/article_f01545a8-383c-5bc6-9d73-fb889ae2569c.html|archive-date=2019-05-31|dead-url=no}}</ref>。法院下令调解后，双方于2010年4月1日达成非公开和解协议。然而，2012年10月，温克尔曼在法庭上承认，他和他的父亲违反了与北面的和解协议，同意支付6.5万美元，如果遵守协议，每月将减少1000美元<ref>{{Cite web|title=North Face, South Butt reach agreement|url=http://www2.stltoday.com/news/local/metro/north-face-south-butt-reach-agreement/article_c096dec5-118f-526a-a9db-244c9ccb0358.html|accessdate=2011-12-08|author=Billhartz Gregorian|date=2010-04-03|first=Cynthia|publisher=STLtoday.com|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120329201612/http://www2.stltoday.com/news/local/metro/north-face-south-butt-reach-agreement/article_c096dec5-118f-526a-a9db-244c9ccb0358.html|archive-date=2012-03-29|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=South Butt Clothing Falls Off a Cliff|url=http://www.courthousenews.com/2012/10/17/51356.htm|accessdate=2012-10-22|date=2012-10-17|publisher=Couthouse News Service|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121028083337/http://www.courthousenews.com/2012/10/17/51356.htm|archive-date=2012-10-28|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

2019年5月，North Face巴西分部的行銷專員{{le|李奧·伯內特·泰勒·邁德|Leo Burnett Tailor Made}}，透露他們將維基百科中的熱門戶外景點照片偷偷替換成帶有North Face產品的照片，試圖讓這些產品在搜尋引擎中[[搜尋引擎最佳化|更為突出]]。經媒體廣泛報導，以及[[維基媒體基金會|維基媒體基金會]]發出批判之下，North Face對此行為予以致歉，而這些[[置入性行銷|-{zh-cn:植入性营销; zh-tw:置入性行銷; zh-hk:植入性營銷}-]]的編輯動作也被回退<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/05/30/business/north-face-wikipedia-leo-burnett.html|title=North Face Apologizes for Adding Its Own Photos to Wikipedia to Promote Its Brand|last=Mervosh|first=Sarah|date=2019-05-30|work=The New York Times|access-date=2019-05-31|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190531001102/https://www.nytimes.com/2019/05/30/business/north-face-wikipedia-leo-burnett.html|archive-date=2019-05-31|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

== 时尚 ==
到1997年，北面服装的购买者已从[[滑雪|滑雪]]、[[登山|登山]]和其他户外活动的爱好者，扩展到了[[纽约|纽约]]的[[饒舌|饒舌]]歌手，但后者只占公司业务的一小部分<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1997/03/09/style/geared-for-the-grocery-or-mount-everest.html|title=Geared for the Grocery, or Mount Everest|author=Szabo|first=Julia|date=1997-03-09|work=New York Times|accessdate=2019-05-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190531172103/https://www.nytimes.com/1997/03/09/style/geared-for-the-grocery-or-mount-everest.html|archive-date=2019-05-31|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

现在，北面的服装成为了一种身份的象征，导致穿着北面服装的人成了抢劫的目标。2010年初，[[韩国|韩国]]也出现了类似的趋势，穿着北面服装的儿童受到欺负或其北面服装被偷<ref>{{Cite web|title=How The North Face Took Over ’90s New York|url=https://www.thecut.com/2018/10/the-north-face-new-york-style.html|accessdate=2019-05-31|author=Takanashi|date=2018-10-31|first=Lei|work=The Cut|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190531143931/https://www.thecut.com/2018/10/the-north-face-new-york-style.html|archive-date=2019-05-31|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.washtimes.com/metro/20050214-104619-4377r.htm|title=Suspects nabbed in jacket, car robberies|date=2005-02-14|work=The Washington Times|pages=2|access-date=2019-06-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070224141723/http://www.washtimes.com/metro/20050214-104619-4377r.htm|archive-date=2007-02-24|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|title=In South Korea, North Face jackets tied to wave of bullying, theft|url=https://latimesblogs.latimes.com/world_now/2012/01/south-korea-teenagers-north-face-fashion-fad-bullying.html|accessdate=2019-05-31|author=Jung-yoon|date=2012-01-16|first=Choi|work=LA Times Blogs - World Now|language=en-US|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181105213049/https://latimesblogs.latimes.com/world_now/2012/01/south-korea-teenagers-north-face-fashion-fad-bullying.html|archivedate=2018-11-05|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

